In the first set of specificity experiments we compared the interaction of F-GNPs with mouse anti-FA antibodies attached to the wells, with non-specific mouse IgG, with BSA and with an empty well (Fig. 6
                     ). This set shows the appearance of GNPs surface plasmon band only in the well with mouse anti-FA antibodies, confirming only mouse anti-FA antibodies can bind F-GNPs. The second set of experiments was designed to test the ability of specific mouse anti-FA antibodies to selectively form an immunocomplex with F-GNP. For this purpose mouse anti-FA antibodies were attached to the wells where solutions of F-GNPs, GNPs and hydrothermally treated GNPs were incubated. Results of these experiments (Fig. 7
                     ) demonstrated that specific interaction of F-GNPs with anti-FA antibody was due to folate residue on the GNP surface formed as a result of HT in the presence of a folate, because of systems without folates shows no specific interaction.
